data.description:
Welcome to 235 Ponderosa Lane in Elizabeth, where the possibilities are endless on this sprawling 1+ acre property. This fixer-upper gem is just 10 minutes from Parker, offering you the perfect blend of country living with convenient access to town.

As you step inside, you'll discover a world of potential. Upstairs, the main living area features 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, providing plenty of room for your family or guests. The open floorplan allows for seamless flow between the living, dining, and kitchen areas, making it an ideal canvas for your personal touch. The basement, partially finished, eagerly awaits your creative vision. With 2 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, a spacious laundry room, and a versatile rec room with walk-out access, you can transform this space into your dream entertainment area, guest suite, or home office.



With an attached 2-car garage, you'll have ample space for your vehicles and storage. No more dealing with the elements during those chilly Colorado winters.

Step outside to the fully fenced backyard, offering a safe and private space for outdoor activities, pets, and kids. And here's the best part – this property is approved for horses and other animals, allowing you to embrace the true spirit of country living right in your backyard.

No need to worry about dirt roads, as this home is conveniently located just off the pavement, ensuring easy access year-round. Whether you're a first-time buyer looking for an affordable entry into the market, an investor seeking a promising project, or someone who values space and potential, this property is an exceptional opportunity.

235 Ponderosa Lane is more than a house; it's a canvas for your dreams and aspirations. Embrace the potential, let your imagination run wild, and turn this into the home you've always envisioned. Don't miss out on this great investment opportunity. Act now and make it yours today!
